<inglise> DIRECTIVE 98/26/EC OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL of 19 May 1998 on settlement finality in payment and securities settlement systems </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENDI JA N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 98/26/E&Uuml; arvelduse l&otilde;plikkuse kohta makse- ja v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemides 19. mai 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENT JA EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 100a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 100a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Monetary Institute (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Rahainstituudi arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189b of the Treaty (4), </inglise>
<eesti> toimides asutamislepingu artiklis 189b s&auml;testatud korras ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas the Lamfalussy report of 1990 to the Governors of the central banks of the Group of Ten Countries demonstrated the important systemic risk inherent in payment systems which operate on the basis of several legal types of payment netting, in particular multilateral netting; whereas the reduction of legal risks associated with participation in real time gross settlement systems is of paramount importance, given the increasing development of these systems; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) 1990. aasta Lamfalussy aruandes k&uuml;mne grupi riikide keskpankade juhatajatele osutati t&auml;htsale s&uuml;steemiriskile, mis on seotud maksete mitme &otilde;igusliku tasaarvelduse viisi, eelk&otilde;ige mitmepoolse tasaarvelduse kasutamisel p&otilde;hinevate makses&uuml;steemidega; reaalajalistes brutoarvelduss&uuml;steemides osalemisega seotud &otilde;iguslike riskide v&auml;hendamine on &uuml;limalt t&auml;htis, arvestades nende s&uuml;steemide j&auml;tkuvat arengut; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas it is also of the utmost importance to reduce the risk associated with participation in securities settlement systems, in particular where there is a close connection between such systems and payment systems; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) samuti on &auml;&auml;rmiselt oluline v&auml;hendada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemides osalemisega seotud riski, eelk&otilde;ige juhul, kui sellised s&uuml;steemid ja makses&uuml;steemid on omavahel tihedalt seotud; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas this Directive aims at contributing to the efficient and cost effective operation of cross-border payment and securities settlement arrangements in the Community, which reinforces the freedom of movement of capital in the internal market; whereas this Directive thereby follows up the progress made towards completion of the internal market, in particular towards the freedom to provide services and liberalisation of capital movements, with a view to the realisation of Economic and Monetary Union; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) k&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on toetada rahvusvaheliste maksete ja v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduste korra t&otilde;husat ja tasuvat toimimist &uuml;henduses, mis tugevdab kapitali liikumise vabadust siseturul; seel&auml;bi j&auml;tkab k&auml;esolev direktiiv edusamme, mis on tehtud siseturu v&auml;ljakujundamise, eelk&otilde;ige teenuste osutamise vabaduse ja kapitali liikumise piirangutest vabastamise suunas, et saavutada majandus- ja rahaliit; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas it is desirable that the laws of the Member States should aim to minimise the disruption to a system caused by insolvency proceedings against a participant in that system; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) on soovitav, et liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide eesm&auml;rk oleks v&otilde;imalikult v&auml;hendada s&uuml;steemi h&auml;ireid, mida p&otilde;hjustavad k&otilde;nealuses s&uuml;steemis osaleja vastu algatatud maksej&otilde;uetusmenetlused; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas a proposal for a Directive on the reorganisation and winding-up of credit institutions submitted in 1985 and amended on 8 February 1988 is still pending before the Council; whereas the Convention on Insolvency Proceedings drawn up on 23 November 1995 by the Member States meeting within the Council explicitly excludes insurance undertakings, credit institutions and investment firms; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) 1985. aastal esitatud ja 8. veebruaril 1988 muudetud ettepaneku suhtes krediidiasutuste &uuml;mberkorraldamist ja l&otilde;petamist k&auml;sitleva direktiivi vastuv&otilde;tmiseks ei ole n&otilde;ukogu veel otsust teinud; n&otilde;ukogus kohtunud liikmesriikide 23. novembril 1995 koostatud maksej&otilde;uetusmenetluse konventsiooni reguleerimisalast arvatakse s&otilde;naselgelt v&auml;lja kindlustusseltsid, krediidiasutused ja investeerimis&uuml;hingud; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas this Directive is intended to cover payment and securities settlement systems of a domestic as well as of a cross-border nature; whereas the Directive is applicable to Community systems and to collateral security constituted by their participants, be they Community or third country participants, in connection with participation in these systems; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) k&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on h&otilde;lmata nii siseriiklikke kui ka rahvusvahelisi makse- ja v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steeme; k&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse &uuml;henduse s&uuml;steemide ja tagatiste suhtes, mida nendes osalejad, olgu siis &uuml;hendusest v&otilde;i kolmandatest riikidest, on andnud seoses nendes s&uuml;steemides osalemisega; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas Member States may apply the provisions of this Directive to their domestic institutions which participate directly in third country systems and to collateral security provided in connection with participation in such systems; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad kohaldada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tteid oma siseriiklike asutuste suhtes, kes osalevad vahetult kolmandate riikide s&uuml;steemides, ja seoses osalemisega sellistes s&uuml;steemides antud tagatiste suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas Member States should be allowed to designate as a system covered by this Directive a system whose main activity is the settlement of securities even if the system to a limited extent also deals with commodity derivatives; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) liikmesriikidel tuleks lubada m&auml;&auml;rata k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavaks selline s&uuml;steem, mille p&otilde;hitegevus on v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarveldused, isegi kui s&uuml;steemis tegeldakse piiratud ulatuses ka kaubap&otilde;histe tuletisv&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas the reduction of systemic risk requires in particular the finality of settlement and the enforceability of collateral security; whereas collateral security is meant to comprise all means provided by a participant to the other participants in the payment and/or securities settlement systems to secure rights and obligations in connection with that system, including repurchase agreements, statutory liens and fiduciary transfers; whereas regulation in national law of the kind of collateral security which can be used should not be affected by the definition of collateral security in this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) s&uuml;steemiriski v&auml;hendamine eeldab eelk&otilde;ige arvelduse l&otilde;plikkust ja tagatise t&auml;itmisele p&ouml;&ouml;ratavust; tagatistena k&auml;sitletakse k&otilde;iki vahendeid, kaasa arvatud tagasiostulepingud, seadusj&auml;rgsed pandi&otilde;igused ja tagatis&otilde;iguste &uuml;leminek usaldusisikule, mida osaleja annab teistele makse- ja/v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemides osalejatele, et tagada selle s&uuml;steemiga seotud &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi; tagatise m&auml;&auml;ratlus k&auml;esolevas direktiivis ei tohiks m&otilde;jutada siseriiklikke eeskirju kasutatavate tagatiste liikide kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas this Directive, by covering collateral security provided in connection with operations of the central banks of the Member States functioning as central banks, including monetary policy operations, assists the European Monetary Institute in its task of promoting the efficiency of cross-border payments with a view to the preparation of the third stage of Economic and Monetary Union and thereby contributes to developing the necessary legal framework in which the future European central bank may develop its policy; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) h&otilde;lmates tagatisi, mis on antud seoses keskpankade &uuml;lesannet t&auml;itvate liikmesriikide keskpankade toimingutega, kaasa arvatud rahapoliitilised meetmed, abistab k&auml;esolev direktiiv Euroopa Rahainstituuti tema &uuml;lesandes t&otilde;hustada v&auml;lismaksete sooritamist, et valmistada ette majandus- ja rahaliidu kolmandat etappi, ning toetab seel&auml;bi vajaliku &otilde;igusliku raamistiku kujundamist, milles tulevane Euroopa Keskpank v&otilde;ib arendada oma rahapoliitikat; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) Whereas transfer orders and their netting should be legally enforceable under all Member States' jurisdictions and binding on third parties; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) maksejuhised ja nende tasaarveldused peaksid olema k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides &otilde;iguslikult t&auml;itmisele p&ouml;&ouml;ratavad ja kolmandatele isikutele siduvad; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) Whereas rules on finality of netting should not prevent systems testing, before the netting takes place, whether orders that have entered the system comply with the rules of that system and allow the settlement of that system to take place; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) tasaarvelduse l&otilde;plikkust k&auml;sitlevad eeskirjad ei tohiks takistada s&uuml;steeme enne tasaarvelduse toimumist kontrollimast, kas s&uuml;steemi sisestatud juhised vastavad k&otilde;nealuse s&uuml;steemi eeskirjadele ja v&otilde;imaldavad teostada tasaarveldust selles s&uuml;steemis; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Whereas nothing in this Directive should prevent a participant or a third party from exercising any right or claim resulting from the underlying transaction which they may have in law to recovery or restitution in respect of a transfer order which has entered a system, e.g. in case of fraud or technical error, as long as this leads neither to the unwinding of netting nor to the revocation of the transfer order in the system; </inglise>
<eesti> 13) mitte miski k&auml;esolevas direktiivis ei tohiks takistada &uuml;htki osalejat ega kolmandat isikut kasutamast v&otilde;imalikke seadusj&auml;rgseid &otilde;igusi v&otilde;i esitamast n&otilde;udeid aluseks oleva tehingu tagaj&auml;rjel s&uuml;steemi sisestatud maksejuhise tagasisaamiseks v&otilde;i tagastamiseks, n&auml;iteks pettuse v&otilde;i tehnilise vea korral, kui see ei p&otilde;hjusta tasaarvelduse ega maksejuhise t&uuml;histamist s&uuml;steemis; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) Whereas it is necessary to ensure that transfer orders cannot be revoked after a moment defined by the rules of the system; </inglise>
<eesti> 14) on vaja tagada, et maksejuhiseid ei saa t&uuml;histada p&auml;rast s&uuml;steemi eeskirjades m&auml;&auml;ratletud ajahetke; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) Whereas it is necessary that a Member State should immediately notify other Member States of the opening of insolvency proceedings against a participant in the system; </inglise>
<eesti> 15) on vaja, et liikmesriik teataks teistele liikmesriikidele viivitamata maksej&otilde;uetusmenetluse algatamisest s&uuml;steemis osaleja vastu; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) Whereas insolvency proceedings should not have a retroactive effect on the rights and obligations of participants in a system; </inglise>
<eesti> 16) maksej&otilde;uetusmenetlustel ei tohiks olla tagasiulatuvat j&otilde;udu s&uuml;steemis osaleja &otilde;iguste ja kohustuste suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> (17) Whereas, in the event of insolvency proceedings against a participant in a system, this Directive furthermore aims at determining which insolvency law is applicable to the rights and obligations of that participant in connection with its participation in a system; </inglise>
<eesti> 17) maksej&otilde;uetusmenetluse korral s&uuml;steemis osaleja vastu on k&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk lisaks sellele m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks, millist maksej&otilde;uetus&otilde;igust kohaldatakse osaleja &otilde;iguste ja kohustuste suhtes seoses tema osalemisega s&uuml;steemis; </eesti>
<inglise> (18) Whereas collateral security should be insulated from the effects of the insolvency law applicable to the insolvent participant; </inglise>
<eesti> 18) maksej&otilde;uetu osaleja suhtes kohaldatav maksej&otilde;uetus&otilde;igus ei tohiks m&otilde;jutada tagatist; </eesti>
<inglise> (19) Whereas the provisions of Article 9(2) should only apply to a register, account or centralized deposit system which evidences the existence of proprietary rights in or for the delivery or transfer of the securities concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> 19) artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 2 s&auml;tteid tuleks kohaldada &uuml;ksnes registri, konto v&otilde;i keskse depositooriumi suhtes, mis t&otilde;endab k&otilde;nealuste v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite suhtes varaliste &otilde;iguste v&otilde;i nende &uuml;leandmise v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmise &otilde;iguste olemasolu; </eesti>
<inglise> (20) Whereas the provisions of Article 9(2) are intended to ensure that if the participant, the central bank of a Member State or the future European central bank has a valid and effective collateral security as determined under the law of the Member State where the relevant register, account or centralized deposit system is located, then the validity and enforceability of that collateral security as against that system (and the operator thereof) and against any other person claiming directly or indirectly through it, should be determined solely under the law of that Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> 20) artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 2 s&auml;tted on m&otilde;eldud tagamaks, et juhul, kui osalejal, liikmesriigi keskpangal v&otilde;i tulevasel Euroopa Keskpangal on kehtiv tagatis selle liikmesriigi &otilde;iguse kohaselt, kus asjakohane register, konto v&otilde;i keskne depositoorium asub, tuleks selle tagatise kehtivust ja t&auml;itmisele p&ouml;&ouml;ratavust selle s&uuml;steemi (ja selle k&auml;itaja) ning k&otilde;ikide muude otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt l&auml;bi selle s&uuml;steemi n&otilde;udeid esitavate isikute suhtes m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks &uuml;ksnes k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi &otilde;iguse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise> (21) Whereas the provisions of Article 9(2) are not intended to prejudice the operation and effect of the law of the Member State under which the securities are constituted or of the law of the Member State where the securities may otherwise be located (including, without limitation, the law concerning the creation, ownership or transfer of such securities or of rights in such securities) and should not be interpreted to mean that any such collateral security will be directly enforceable or be capable of being recognised in any such Member State otherwise than in accordance with the law of that Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> 21) artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 2 s&auml;tete eesm&auml;rk ei ole piirata selle liikmesriigi &otilde;iguse kohaldamist ja m&otilde;ju, kelle &otilde;iguse alusel on v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid v&auml;lja lastud, ega selle liikmesriigi &otilde;iguse kohaldamist ja m&otilde;ju, kus v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid muul juhul asuvad (sealhulgas piiramata selliste v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite v&otilde;i nendega seotud &otilde;iguste v&auml;ljalaskmist, omamist v&otilde;i &uuml;leandmist k&auml;sitlevate &otilde;igusaktide kohaldamist), ning neid s&auml;tteid ei tohiks t&otilde;lgendada nii, et iga selline tagatis on vahetult t&auml;itmisele p&ouml;&ouml;ratav v&otilde;i tunnustatav m&otilde;nes sellises liikmesriigis ka muul viisil kui koosk&otilde;las selle liikmesriigi &otilde;igusega; </eesti>
<inglise> (22) Whereas it is desirable that Member States endeavour to establish sufficient links between all the securities settlement systems covered by this Directive with a view towards promoting maximum transparency and legal certainty of transactions relating to securities; </inglise>
<eesti> 22) on soovitav, et liikmesriigid &uuml;ritavad luua piisavaid sidemeid k&otilde;ikide k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemide vahel, et saavutada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega seotud tehingute osas v&otilde;imalikult suur l&auml;bipaistvus ja &otilde;iguskindlus; </eesti>
<inglise> (23) Whereas the adoption of this Directive constitutes the most appropriate way of realising the abovementioned objectives and does not go beyond what is necessary to achieve them, </inglise>
<eesti> 23) k&auml;esoleva direktiivi vastuv&otilde;tmine on k&otilde;ige sobivam viis eespool nimetatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks, h&otilde;lmamata rohkem kui nende saavutamiseks h&auml;davajalik, </eesti>
<inglise> HAVE ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION I </inglise>
<eesti> I JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> SCOPE AND DEFINITIONS </inglise>
<eesti> REGULEERIMISALA JA M&Otilde;ISTED </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of this Directive shall apply to: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) any system as defined in Article 2(a), governed by the law of a Member State and operating in any currency, the ecu or in various currencies which the system converts one against another; </inglise>
<eesti> a) iga artikli 2 punktis a m&auml;&auml;ratletud s&uuml;steemi suhtes, mida reguleerib liikmesriigi &otilde;igus ja mis toimib mis tahes v&auml;&auml;ringus, ek&uuml;&uuml;des v&otilde;i erinevates v&auml;&auml;ringutes, mida arvestatakse s&uuml;steemis teineteise suhtes &uuml;mber; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) any participant in such a system; </inglise>
<eesti> b) iga sellises s&uuml;steemis osaleja suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) collateral security provided in connection with: </inglise>
<eesti> c) tagatise suhtes, mis antakse seoses: </eesti>
<inglise> - participation in a system, or </inglise>
<eesti> - s&uuml;steemis osalemisega v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - operations of the central banks of the Member States in their functions as central banks. </inglise>
<eesti> - liikmesriikide keskpankade toimingutega nende t&auml;ites keskpanga &uuml;lesannet. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) 'system' shall mean a formal arrangement: </inglise>
<eesti> a) s&uuml;steem - vormiline struktuur: </eesti>
<inglise> - between three or more participants, without counting a possible settlement agent, a possible central counterparty, a possible clearing house or a possible indirect participant, with common rules and standardised arrangements for the execution of transfer orders between the participants, </inglise>
<eesti> - kolme v&otilde;i enama osaleja vahel, arvestamata v&otilde;imalikku arveldusagenti, v&otilde;imalikku keskset osalejat, v&otilde;imalikku arvelduskoda v&otilde;i v&otilde;imalikku kaudset osalejat, kusjuures on olemas &uuml;hised eeskirjad ja &uuml;htne kord maksejuhiste t&auml;itmiseks osalejate vahel, </eesti>
<inglise> - governed by the law of a Member State chosen by the participants; the participants may, however, only choose the law of a Member State in which at least one of them has its head office, and </inglise>
<eesti> - mida reguleerib osalejate valitud liikmesriigi &otilde;igus; osalejad v&otilde;ivad siiski valida &uuml;ksnes sellise liikmesriigi &otilde;iguse, kus asub v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he osaleja peakontor, ja </eesti>
<inglise> - designated, without prejudice to other more stringent conditions of general application laid down by national law, as a system and notified to the Commission by the Member State whose law is applicable, after that Member State is satisfied as to the adequacy of the rules of the system. </inglise>
<eesti> - mille on s&uuml;steemiks m&auml;&auml;ranud ja sellest komisjonile teatanud p&auml;rast s&uuml;steemi eeskirjade asjakohasuses veendumist see liikmesriik, kelle &otilde;igust kohaldatakse, ilma et see piiraks muude, siseriiklikes &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud rangemate &uuml;ldkohaldatavate tingimuste kohaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Subject to the conditions in the first subparagraph, a Member State may designate as a system such a formal arrangement whose business consists of the execution of transfer orders as defined in the second indent of (i) and which to a limited extent executes orders relating to other financial instruments, when that Member State considers that such a designation is warranted on grounds of systemic risk. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt esimese l&otilde;igu tingimustele v&otilde;ib liikmesriik s&uuml;steemiks m&auml;&auml;rata sellise vormilise struktuuri, kelle tegevus koosneb punkti i teises taandes m&auml;&auml;ratletud maksejuhiste t&auml;itmisest ja kes t&auml;idab piiratud ulatuses muude finantsvahenditega seotud juhiseid, kui k&otilde;nealune liikmesriik leiab, et m&auml;&auml;ramine on s&uuml;steemiriski t&otilde;ttu &otilde;igustatud. </eesti>
<inglise> A Member State may also on a case-by-case basis designate as a system such a formal arrangement between two participants, without counting a possible settlement agent, a possible central counterparty, a possible clearing house or a possible indirect participant, when that Member State considers that such a designation is warranted on grounds of systemic risk; </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti v&otilde;ib liikmesriik iga &uuml;ksikjuhu puhul eraldi m&auml;&auml;rata s&uuml;steemiks vormilise struktuuri kahe osaleja vahel, arvestamata v&otilde;imalikku arveldusagenti, v&otilde;imalikku keskset osalejat, v&otilde;imalikku arvelduskoda v&otilde;i v&otilde;imalikku kaudset osalejat, kui k&otilde;nealune liikmesriik leiab, et m&auml;&auml;ramine on s&uuml;steemiriski t&otilde;ttu &otilde;igustatud; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) 'institution' shall mean: </inglise>
<eesti> b) asutus: </eesti>
<inglise> - a credit institution as defined in the first indent of Article 1 of Directive 77/780/EEC (5) including the institutions set out in the list in Article 2(2) thereof, or </inglise>
<eesti> - krediidiasutus direktiivi 77/780/EM&Uuml; artikli 1 esimeses taandes m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses, sealhulgas k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi artikli 2 l&otilde;ike 2 loendis s&auml;testatud asutused, </eesti>
<inglise> - an investment firm as defined in point 2 of Article 1 of Directive 93/22/EEC (6) excluding the institutions set out in the list in Article 2(2) (a) to (k) thereof, or </inglise>
