<inglise> If a system is supervised in accordance with national legislation and only executes transfer orders as defined in the second indent of (i), as well as payments resulting from such orders, a Member State may decide that undertakings which participate in such a system and which have responsibility for discharging the financial obligations arising from transfer orders within this system, can be considered institutions, provided that at least three participants of this system are covered by the categories referred to in the first subparagraph and that such a decision is warranted on grounds of systemic risk; </inglise>
<eesti> Kui s&uuml;steemi j&auml;rele valvatakse koosk&otilde;las siseriikliku &otilde;igusega ja see t&auml;idab &uuml;ksnes punkti i teises taandes m&auml;&auml;ratletud maksejuhiseid ning teostab sellistest juhistest tulenevaid makseid, v&otilde;ib liikmesriik otsustada, et sellises s&uuml;steemis osalevaid ettev&otilde;tjaid, kes vastutavad maksejuhistest tulenevate rahaliste kohustuste t&auml;itmise eest selles s&uuml;steemis, v&otilde;ib k&auml;sitleda asutustena, tingimusel et v&auml;hemalt kolm selles s&uuml;steemis osalejat kuulub esimeses l&otilde;igus nimetatud liikidesse ja k&otilde;nealune otsus on s&uuml;steemiriski t&otilde;ttu &otilde;igustatud; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) 'central counterparty' shall mean an entity which is interposed between the institutions in a system and which acts as the exclusive counterparty of these institutions with regard to their transfer orders; </inglise>
<eesti> c) keskne osaleja - &uuml;ksus s&uuml;steemis osalevate asutuste vahel, kes toimib nende asutuste suhtes eraldiseisva osapoolena nende asutuste maksejuhiste osas; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) 'settlement agent' shall mean an entity providing to institutions and/or a central counterparty participating in systems, settlement accounts through which transfer orders within such systems are settled and, as the case may be, extending credit to those institutions and/or central counterparties for settlement purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> d) arveldusagent - &uuml;ksus, kes pakub s&uuml;steemis osalevatele asutustele ja/v&otilde;i kesksele osalejale arvelduskontosid, mille kaudu maksejuhiseid sellistes s&uuml;steemides arveldatakse, ja annab vajaduse korral nendele asutustele ja/v&otilde;i kesksetele osalejatele arveldamise eesm&auml;rgil krediiti; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) 'clearing house' shall mean an entity responsible for the calculation of the net positions of institutions, a possible central counterparty and/or a possible settlement agent; </inglise>
<eesti> e) arvelduskoda - &uuml;ksus, kes vastutab asutuste, v&otilde;imaliku keskse osaleja ja/v&otilde;i v&otilde;imaliku arveldusagendi netopositsioonide arvutamise eest; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) 'participant' shall mean an institution, a central counterparty, a settlement agent or a clearing house. </inglise>
<eesti> f) osaleja - asutus, keskne osaleja, arveldusagent v&otilde;i arvelduskoda. </eesti>
<inglise> According to the rules of the system, the same participant may act as a central counterparty, a settlement agent or a clearing house or carry out part or all of these tasks. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt s&uuml;steemi eeskirjadele v&otilde;ib &uuml;ks ja seesama osaleja toimida keskse osaleja, arveldusagendi v&otilde;i arvelduskojana v&otilde;i t&auml;ita k&otilde;iki neid &uuml;lesandeid v&otilde;i osa neist. </eesti>
<inglise> A Member State may decide that for the purposes of this Directive an indirect participant may be considered a participant if it is warranted on the grounds of systemic risk and on condition that the indirect participant is known to the system; </inglise>
<eesti> Kui see on s&uuml;steemiriski t&otilde;ttu &otilde;igustatud, v&otilde;ib liikmesriik otsustada, et k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamisel v&otilde;ib kaudset osalejat k&auml;sitleda osalejana, tingimusel et kaudset osalejat tuntakse s&uuml;steemis; </eesti>
<inglise> (g) 'indirect participant' shall mean a credit institution as defined in the first indent of (b) with a contractual relationship with an institution participating in a system executing transfer orders as defined in the first indent of (i) which enables the abovementioned credit institution to pass transfer orders through the system; </inglise>
<eesti> g) kaudne osaleja - punkti b esimeses taandes m&auml;&auml;ratletud krediidiasutus, kellel on lepinguline suhe sellises s&uuml;steemis osaleva asutusega, kus t&auml;idetakse punkti i esimeses taandes m&auml;&auml;ratletud maksejuhiseid, v&otilde;imaldades eespool nimetatud krediidiasutusel suunata maksejuhiseid l&auml;bi s&uuml;steemi; </eesti>
<inglise> (h) 'securities' shall mean all instruments referred to in section B of the Annex to Directive 93/22/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> h) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid - k&otilde;ik direktiivi 93/22/EM&Uuml; lisa B jaos nimetatud vahendid; </eesti>
<inglise> (i) 'transfer order' shall mean: </inglise>
<eesti> i) maksejuhis: </eesti>
<inglise> - any instruction by a participant to place at the disposal of a recipient an amount of money by means of a book entry on the accounts of a credit institution, a central bank or a settlement agent, or any instruction which results in the assumption or discharge of a payment obligation as defined by the rules of the system, or </inglise>
<eesti> - osaleja mis tahes korraldus anda saaja k&auml;sutusse teatav hulk raha, tehes raamatupidamiskande krediidiasutuse, keskpanga v&otilde;i arveldusagendi kontodele, v&otilde;i mis tahes korraldus, millest tuleneb maksekohustuse v&otilde;tmine v&otilde;i selle t&auml;itmine, nagu m&auml;&auml;ratletud s&uuml;steemi eeskirjades, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - an instruction by a participant to transfer the title to, or interest in, a security or securities by means of a book entry on a register, or otherwise; </inglise>
<eesti> - osaleja mis tahes korraldus anda &uuml;le v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omandi- v&otilde;i muu &otilde;igus, tehes registrisse raamatupidamiskande v&otilde;i muul viisil; </eesti>
<inglise> (j) 'insolvency proceedings' shall mean any collective measure provided for in the law of a Member State, or a third country, either to wind up the participant or to reorganise it, where such measure involves the suspending of, or imposing limitations on, transfers or payments; </inglise>
<eesti> j) maksej&otilde;uetusmenetlus - liikmesriigi v&otilde;i kolmanda riigi &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud mis tahes &uuml;hismeetmed osaleja l&otilde;petamiseks v&otilde;i &uuml;mberkorraldamiseks, kui selliste meetmetega kaasneb &uuml;lekannete v&otilde;i maksete peatamine v&otilde;i piiramine; </eesti>
<inglise> (k) 'netting' shall mean the conversion into one net claim or one net obligation of claims and obligations resulting from transfer orders which a participant or participants either issue to, or receive from, one or more other participants with the result that only a net claim can be demanded or a net obligation be owed; </inglise>
<eesti> k) tasaarveldus - osaleja v&otilde;i osalejate poolt &uuml;hele v&otilde;i mitmele teisele osalejale antud v&otilde;i neilt saadud maksejuhistest tulenevate n&otilde;uete ja kohustuste &uuml;mberarvestamine &uuml;heks neton&otilde;udeks v&otilde;i &uuml;heks netokohustuseks, mille tulemusena saab sisse n&otilde;uda &uuml;ksnes neton&otilde;ude v&otilde;i v&otilde;lgneda netokohustuse; </eesti>
<inglise> (l) 'settlement account' shall mean an account at a central bank, a settlement agent or a central counterparty used to hold funds and securities and to settle transactions between participants in a system; </inglise>
